97 /**
98  * @brief Test function to compose/use CAN messages.
99  *
100  */
101 void testMessageComposition(void) {
102  CAN_BUFFER_ELEMENT_s canMessage;
103  uint8_t dataWord;
104  uint8_t dataByte;
105  uint16_t data16;
106  uint8_t data8;
107  uint8_t command;
108  uint8_t id;
109  uint8_t tries;
110 
111  /* Do as if there is a message in the queue */
112  OS_GetNumberOfStoredMessagesInQueue_IgnoreAndReturn(1u);
113  MPU_xQueueReceive_IgnoreAndReturn(1u);
114  OS_ReceiveFromQueue_IgnoreAndReturn(OS_SUCCESS);
115 
116  canMessage.id = 0x22u;
117  for (uint8_t i = 1u; i <= 8u; i++) {
118  canMessage.data[i] = i;
119  }
120  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_ResetCanData(NULL_PTR));
121  /* Reset must set all data to 0 */
122  TEST_I165C_ResetCanData(&canMessage);
123  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < 8u; i++) {
124  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, canMessage.data[i]);
125  }
126 
127  data16 = 666u;
128  dataWord = I165C_DW1;
129  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_WriteDataWord(dataWord, data16, NULL_PTR););
130  /* Test that data is written correctly to CAN frame */
131  TEST_I165C_WriteDataWord(dataWord, data16, &canMessage);
132  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x9Au, canMessage.data[1u]);
133  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x02u, canMessage.data[2u]);
134  dataWord = I165C_DW2;
135  TEST_I165C_WriteDataWord(dataWord, data16, &canMessage);
136  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x9Au, canMessage.data[3u]);
137  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x02u, canMessage.data[4u]);
138 
139  for (uint8_t i = 1u; i <= 4u; i++) {
140  canMessage.data[i] = i;
141  }
142  data16 = 0u;
143  dataWord = I165C_DW1;
144  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_ReadDataWord(dataWord, NULL_PTR, canMessage));
145  /* Test that dataword data is read correctly from usual CAN frame */
146  TEST_I165C_ReadDataWord(dataWord, &data16, canMessage);
147  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x201u, data16);
148  data16 = 0u;
149  dataWord = I165C_DW2;
150  TEST_I165C_ReadDataWord(dataWord, &data16, canMessage);
151  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x403u, data16);
152 
153  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i <= 5u; i++) {
154  canMessage.data[i] = i + 1u;
155  }
156  data16 = 0u;
157  dataWord = I165C_DW1;
158  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_ReadDataWordImdInfo(dataWord, NULL_PTR, canMessage));
159  /* Test that dataword data is read correctly from special IMD_Info CAN frame */
160  TEST_I165C_ReadDataWordImdInfo(dataWord, &data16, canMessage);
161  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x201u, data16);
162  data16 = 0u;
163  dataWord = I165C_DW2;
164  TEST_I165C_ReadDataWordImdInfo(dataWord, &data16, canMessage);
165  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x403u, data16);
166  data16 = 0u;
167  dataWord = I165C_DW3;
168  TEST_I165C_ReadDataWordImdInfo(dataWord, &data16, canMessage);
169  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x605u, data16);
170 
171  for (uint8_t i = 1u; i <= 4u; i++) {
172  canMessage.data[i] = i;
173  }
174  data8 = 0u;
175  dataByte = I165C_DB1;
176  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_ReadDataByte(dataByte, NULL_PTR, canMessage));
177  /* Test that databyte data is read correctly from usual CAN frame */
178  TEST_I165C_ReadDataByte(dataByte, &data8, canMessage);
179  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x1u, data8);
180  data8 = 0u;
181  dataByte = I165C_DB2;
182  TEST_I165C_ReadDataByte(dataByte, &data8, canMessage);
183  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x2u, data8);
184  data8 = 0u;
185  dataByte = I165C_DB3;
186  TEST_I165C_ReadDataByte(dataByte, &data8, canMessage);
187  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x3u, data8);
188  data8 = 0u;
189  dataByte = I165C_DB4;
190  TEST_I165C_ReadDataByte(dataByte, &data8, canMessage);
191  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0x4u, data8);
192 
193  id = 0xA;
194  command = 0xB;
195  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_WriteCmd(id, command, NULL_PTR));
196  /* Test that cmd is written correctly to CAN frame */
197  TEST_I165C_WriteCmd(id, command, &canMessage);
198  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0xAu, canMessage.id);
199  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(I165C_RX_MESSAGE_IDENTIFIER_TYPE, canMessage.idType);
200  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0xBu, canMessage.data[0u]);
201 
202  /* Check assertion of invalid parameter */
203  canMessage.data[0u] = 0xA;
204  command = 0xA;
205  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_CheckResponse(command, NULL_PTR));
206 
207  /* Check that response ID corresponds to awaited acknowledge */
208  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID;
209  canMessage.data[0u] = 0xA;
210  command = 0xA;
211  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, TEST_I165C_CheckResponse(command, &canMessage));
212 
213  /* Check that response ID does not correspond to awaited acknowledge */
214  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID;
215  canMessage.data[0u] = 0xA;
216  command = 0xB;
217  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, TEST_I165C_CheckResponse(command, &canMessage));
218 
219  /* Check that response failed if ID is not CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID, even if response matches command */
220  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_INFO_ID;
221  canMessage.data[0u] = 0xA;
222  command = 0xA;
223  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, TEST_I165C_CheckResponse(command, &canMessage));
224 
225  /* Check that response failed if ID is not CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID, if respose does not match command */
226  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_INFO_ID;
227  canMessage.data[0u] = 0xA;
228  command = 0xB;
229  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, TEST_I165C_CheckResponse(command, &canMessage));
230 
231  canMessage.id = I165C_MESSAGETYPE_IMD_INFO;
232  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_GetImdInfo(NULL_PTR));
233  /* Test that an IMD_info frame was received on CAN */
234  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, TEST_I165C_GetImdInfo(&canMessage));
235  canMessage.id = I165C_MESSAGETYPE_IMD_INFO + 1u;
236  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, TEST_I165C_GetImdInfo(&canMessage));
237 
238  /* Test if CAN data indicated that iso165c is not initialized */
239  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < 8u; i++) {
240  canMessage.data[i] = 0u;
241  }
242  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, TEST_I165C_IsSelfTestFinished(canMessage));
243 
244  /* Test if CAN data indicated that iso165c is not initialized */
245  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < 8u; i++) {
246  canMessage.data[i] = 0x00u;
247  }
248  /*
249  * D_IMC_STATUS is located in byte 2 and byte 3 of CAN message:
250  * Bit 4: Self test running -> set to 1 */
251  canMessage.data[2u] |= (1u << I165C_SELFTEST_RUNNING_SHIFT);
252  /* D_VIFC_STATUS is located in byte 4 and byte 5 of CAN message
253  * Bit 0: Insulation measurement active -> set to 0
254  * Bit 12: Self-test long executed -> set to 0
255  * Bit 13: Self-test short executed -> set to 0
256  */
257  canMessage.data[4u] |= (0u << I165C_INSULATION_MEASUREMENT_STATUS_SHIFT);
258  canMessage.data[5u] |=
259  (0u << (I165C_IMC_SELFTEST_OVERALL_SCENARIO_SHIFT - 8u)); /* Subtract 8 because upper byte is used */
260  canMessage.data[5u] |=
261  (0u << (I165C_IMC_SELFTEST_PARAMETERCONFIG_SCENARIO_SHIFT - 8u)); /* Subtract 8 because upper byte is used */
262 
263  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, TEST_I165C_IsSelfTestFinished(canMessage));
264 
265  /* ----------- Test function that waits for acknowledge -----------------*/
266 
267  /* Check for invalid function parameters */
268  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, NULL_PTR, NULL_PTR));
269  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, NULL_PTR, &canMessage));
270  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, &tries, NULL_PTR));
271 
272  /* Acknowledge arrived */
273  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID;
274  tries = 0u;
275  command = 0xA;
276  canMessage.data[0] = 0xA;
277  bool ackReceived = false;
278 
279  ackReceived = TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, &tries, &canMessage);
280  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, ackReceived);
281  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0u, tries);
282 
283  /* Acknowledge not arrived, increment try counter */
284  canMessage.id = CANRX_IMD_RESPONSE_ID;
285  tries = 0u;
286  command = 0xA;
287  canMessage.data[0] = 0xB;
288 
289  ackReceived = TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, &tries, &canMessage);
290  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(1u, tries);
291  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, ackReceived);
292 
293  /* Acknowledge not arrived, and allowed number of tries made, restart
294  * Initialization (go to self test) */
295  tries = I165C_TRANSMISSION_ATTEMPTS - 1u;
296  command = 0xA;
297  canMessage.data[0] = 0xB;
298 
299  ackReceived = TEST_I165C_CheckAcknowledgeArrived(command, &tries, &canMessage);
300  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(I165C_TRANSMISSION_ATTEMPTS, tries);
301  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, ackReceived);
302 }
